The paper discusses the application of deep learning and reinforcement learning techniques in mining biological data, which falls under the intersection of computer science and biology. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions specific application domains such as bioimaging and medical imaging, which suggest a possible fit with cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper also discusses brain-machine interfaces and omics data, which could potentially fall under q-bio.TO (Tissues and Organs) and q-bio.QM (Molecular Networks), respectively.
